  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pancreatic cancer has a high mortality rate. Patients with an intended curative resection
      show a median survival of 17-23 months. Therefore, quality of life is very important in this
      patient group. In this study, the effect of pancreatic surgery on quality of life is
      measured.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
